reviews.text: it is pretty ok la, it could be even better if the price was cheaper.
Great deal at tea time. $69+10% for all you can eat hotpot between 2-4pm. Food tasted good. Hot pot soup tasted very light. Good service and comfortable seating.

What is it exactly? It is a buffet that you eat all you can within a time limit of 90 mins from the time you walk in below $200. The soup base from the menu sounds like Hot Pot restaurant which specialized beef. However, it isn't, it is like a Japanese Sukiyaki where there is only flavor in the soup. The main course is beef. I suggest choosing at least one above basic grade. When you ask for a refill, make sure you ask for the correct grade of beef. Otherwise, you will only serve as the basic grade. When it comes to veg. there are lots of variety to choose from. You can even mix your own sauce to boost the taste. Desert is ice-cream. You can eat all you can. Everything in the restaurant is refillable.
All you can eat
Good price , even cheapest package , beef is tender , best amount those shabu buffet
